# Curator Project Rules

Follow these rules when working on the Curator codebase:

## General
- Use TypeScript for all server and client code.
- Prefer functional components and Composition API in Vue.
- Use Vuetify 3 components for UI.

## Architecture Rules
- Use the **Modular Architecture** pattern.
- Place server logic in `server/modules/[module-name]/`.
- Place client components in `client/src/modules/[module-name]/components/`.
- Ensure every new module has a `README.md` for AI guidance.
- Follow the **Model -> Server -> UI** phased development workflow.

## Logic Rules
- Always scope `Project` queries by `accountId`.
- Enforce `WRITE` role checks for mutations in resolvers.
- Regsiter modular schemas in `server/schema/index.ts`.
- Register modular resolvers in `server/resolvers/index.ts`.
- Keep `App.vue` clean by delegating UI to modular components.

## GraphQL
- All API changes must be reflected in `server/schema/index.ts`.
- Keep resolvers thin; move complex logic to `server/service.ts` or dedicated logic files.
- Always handle authentication by checking `context.user`.

## Database (Prisma)
- Never modify the database directly; always use `prisma/schema.prisma` and migrations.
- When working with vectors, remember they are currently `Unsupported` in Prisma schema and may require raw SQL for similarity searches.
- Dimensions for `xenova_all_minilm_l6_v2` is 384.

## AI / LangChain
- Use the established patterns in `server/langchain.ts` for RAG operations.
- Follow the `Chunk` and `FileData` relationship for document processing.

## Code Style
- Use 2-space indentation.
- Use `import` instead of `require`.
- Provide meaningful error messages via GraphQL errors.
